Basic CSS selector 
    selector { property: value }; 
    declaration starts with left curly brace and ends with the right curly brace


Box-Model content -> padding -> border -> margin
    - content -box : your content
    - padding:  space in-between the content and its border
    - margin: spacing outside the border 

Padding/Margin CSS
    CSS : top right bottom left / top/bottom right/left

Border CSS
    CSS : size, color, style/type

Positioning CSS
    - Static: default; renders the element in order of the document
    - Relative: positioned relative to normal position (top, left, right, bottom)
    - Absolute: target position inside a relative element
    - Fixed: position to the browser window
    - Initial: sets to default value
    - Inherit: will inherit property of its parent element